<br>
You have a source to back this information up?  It was my understanding that the Administration refused to &quot;certify&quot; North Korea in compliance with the Agreed Framework because NK was not allowing the IAEA Full access to the Yongbyon nuclear reactor.  They did however waive taking action on it in the interests of national security and continued to supply America's requirements under the Bilateral *cough* Treaty.<br>
<br>
  It was not until NK admitted that they were actively pursuing the nuclear program, that funding was halted.  The Program itself would have been obvious under the Agreed Framework, if North Korea had been in full compliance allowing inspections, but they were still dragging their feet on that issue after 9 years.  &lt;-- Sound familiar to anyone? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204898">Ayiar Frullaniaceae</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
